WEBVTT

00:38.480 --> 00:40.146
I got everything you need.

00:40.148 --> 00:42.108
Scarves aren't just for warmth.
They're for style.

00:45.654 --> 00:47.287
<i>My name is Nick Barrow.</i>

00:50.559 --> 00:52.325
<i>And I plan heists.</i>

00:52.327 --> 00:56.129
...and scarves! Fedoras. Come here.
I got ties...

00:58.433 --> 01:01.634
<i>There's a few rules to keep
in mind when planning a job.</i>

01:01.636 --> 01:03.436
Scarves, hats!

01:03.438 --> 01:06.506
<i>The easiest place to hide
is in plain sight.</i>

01:06.508 --> 01:08.475
Got it.
Whatcha got, sir, huh?

01:08.477 --> 01:11.110
I got ties!
I got fedoras!

01:11.112 --> 01:12.912
<i>Design the job in a way</i>

01:12.914 --> 01:14.481
<i>so that no one gets hurt.</i>

01:19.621 --> 01:21.354
<i>Timing is everything.</i>

01:25.460 --> 01:27.560
Let's go! Step up!

01:29.498 --> 01:33.166
<i>Finally, every mark has a
weakness that can be exploited.</i>

01:34.836 --> 01:37.270
<i>You just gotta find it.</i>

01:40.642 --> 01:42.509
- Yeah?
<i>- It's Alejandro.</i>

01:42.511 --> 01:44.410
<i>I am interested in the job.</i>

01:45.447 --> 01:46.746
<i>Are you ready to meet?</i>

01:48.550 --> 01:49.830
I am now.

01:52.954 --> 01:56.389
<i>The criminal underworld
is a complicated ecosystem.</i>

01:56.391 --> 01:59.058
<i>Everyone relies on
each other just to survive.</i>

02:00.695 --> 02:03.029
<i>It all starts
with your bottom feeders.</i>

02:03.031 --> 02:05.698
<i>They're always on the lookout
for opportunities.</i>

02:05.700 --> 02:07.534
<i>They find the job.</i>

02:07.536 --> 02:09.235
<i>This guy is Jimmy Lincoln.</i>

02:10.572 --> 02:12.305
<i>Then it moves up to me.</i>

02:12.307 --> 02:15.675
<i>I design the plan of
how to pull off the heist.</i>

02:15.677 --> 02:17.510
<i>Every little detail,</i>

02:17.512 --> 02:18.778
<i>inside and out.</i>

02:20.515 --> 02:21.881
<i>And finally at the top</i>

02:21.883 --> 02:23.483
<i>sits the buyer,</i>

02:23.485 --> 02:25.752
<i>the one who actually
pulls off the job</i>

02:25.754 --> 02:27.654
<i>and takes all the risk.</i>

02:27.656 --> 02:29.222
$30,000 up front.

02:30.725 --> 02:32.759
30,000.

02:32.761 --> 02:34.994
I tell you how to get in.
I tell you how to get out.

02:34.996 --> 02:36.963
Everything in between is on you.

02:38.767 --> 02:41.267
So we just gotta trust you.

02:41.269 --> 02:42.769
Is that it?

02:42.771 --> 02:44.504
Listen to me, Nick.

02:44.506 --> 02:46.339
If you want my money,

02:46.341 --> 02:48.775
I'm going to need something
more reassuring than that.

02:48.777 --> 02:51.044
Alejandro,

02:51.046 --> 02:52.946
I'm not here to talk you
into this.

02:54.182 --> 02:56.115
I'm here to let you do this.

02:56.117 --> 02:57.817
It's yes or no.

03:00.388 --> 03:02.789
The 250,000
is in an evidence locker

03:02.791 --> 03:04.123
at the Fulton County Courthouse,

03:04.125 --> 03:05.792
and I'm gonna tell you
how to take it.

03:05.794 --> 03:08.528
If something
unexpected happens?

03:08.530 --> 03:11.698
If I do my job right, it won't.
And if it does?

03:11.700 --> 03:13.933
Doesn't come with
a money-back guarantee, kid.

03:15.103 --> 03:16.636
But having said that,

03:16.638 --> 03:18.705
I make sure you go in
with everything that you need...

03:18.707 --> 03:21.774
access codes, schematics,
schedules, equipment.

03:21.776 --> 03:23.910
Once we start,

03:23.912 --> 03:26.212
how much time do we have
to get to the spot?

03:26.214 --> 03:28.615
Fifteen minutes.
It's tight but doable.

03:41.296 --> 03:42.996
You miss your window,

03:42.998 --> 03:44.564
that's it.

03:44.566 --> 03:45.832
You want a second chance,

03:45.834 --> 03:48.434
I start all over.

03:48.436 --> 03:50.436
You pay me again.

03:53.575 --> 03:55.908
Oh, boy, you better be good.

03:55.910 --> 03:58.845
Look, guys, this is like nothing
that you've ever done before.

03:59.914 --> 04:01.314
The timing here is everything.

04:01.316 --> 04:03.416
Once you start,
you cannot stop.

04:28.510 --> 04:30.276
And once we're there?

04:30.278 --> 04:31.978
You will have exactly
the amount of time

04:31.980 --> 04:34.180
it takes a traffic light
to go from green to red

04:34.182 --> 04:36.416
and back again...
three minutes.

04:44.693 --> 04:46.125
I want you to think of it

04:46.127 --> 04:49.262
like it's a, uh...
a magic trick.

04:51.633 --> 04:54.400
Half of it is engineering.

04:54.402 --> 04:55.802
And the other half?

04:55.804 --> 04:56.936
Magic.

05:24.566 --> 05:26.999
Freeze! Clear!

05:28.069 --> 05:29.068
What the hell's going on?

05:29.070 --> 05:30.203
Is your cargo secure?

05:30.205 --> 05:32.205
Cargo, uh?

05:32.207 --> 05:34.741
My rig's empty.
I'm here to pick up.

06:22.724 --> 06:24.490
Whoo-hoo!

07:05.300 --> 07:06.399
Pack it up.

07:33.228 --> 07:34.660
<i>I was fucked,</i>

07:34.662 --> 07:37.063
<i>and I didn't even know it.</i>

07:37.065 --> 07:38.798
<i>Perhaps the reason
any of this happened</i>

07:38.800 --> 07:40.366
<i>is because I was distracted.</i>

07:42.070 --> 07:43.870
<i>Catherine Jill Barrow,</i>

07:43.872 --> 07:46.372
<i>otherwise known as Cate,
my daughter.</i>

07:46.374 --> 07:48.207
<i>Sure, she could pick me
out of a crowd,</i>

07:48.209 --> 07:50.877
<i>but we never really spent
any time together.</i>

07:50.879 --> 07:53.045
<i>No one loves that kid
more than me,</i>

07:53.047 --> 07:56.716
<i>but our situation
is a little, uh... complicated.</i>

08:03.591 --> 08:05.691
Our boss wants to renegotiate.

08:05.693 --> 08:07.393
You're not getting
a dime from me.

08:11.733 --> 08:13.900
<i>So the deal is this...</i>

08:13.902 --> 08:16.602
<i>I protect her
and provide from afar,</i>

08:16.604 --> 08:19.839
<i>while my ex, Lucy,
takes care of the day-to-day.</i>

08:19.841 --> 08:23.676
<i>Keep my world
out of her world.</i>

08:23.678 --> 08:26.178
<i>It's better for everyone
the more I stay removed,</i>

08:26.180 --> 08:27.446
<i>especially Cate.</i>

08:29.083 --> 08:30.716
<i>She's a good kid.</i>

08:30.718 --> 08:32.217
<i>She's growing up right.</i>

08:32.220 --> 08:33.852
<i>But she just turned 16</i>

08:33.855 --> 08:36.322
<i>and developed a complete
lack of judgment.</i>

08:38.293 --> 08:39.725
<i>The charge was
underage drinking,</i>

08:39.727 --> 08:41.360
<i>hardly a high crime,</i>

08:41.361 --> 08:43.282
<i>but I'd like her
to have a direction.</i>

08:45.300 --> 08:47.400
<i>One thing's for sure...</i>

08:47.402 --> 08:49.502
<i>I want her to have
a better life.</i>

08:54.609 --> 08:56.909
<i>In my line of work,
there's not many people</i>

08:56.911 --> 08:58.411
<i>you can trust for advice.</i>

08:58.413 --> 09:00.713
<i>Thankfully, I have Harper.</i>

09:00.715 --> 09:02.081
<i>He got me into this business,</i>

09:02.083 --> 09:03.582
<i>and he's my best friend.</i>

09:03.584 --> 09:05.451
Still hanging out with cops?

09:05.453 --> 09:08.587
Murph is one of the most
respected guys on the force.

09:08.589 --> 09:10.589
We've known each other
since we were kids.

09:10.591 --> 09:12.291
He's still a cop.
Makes me nervous.

09:12.293 --> 09:14.994
Good. We're crooks.
They should make you nervous.

09:14.996 --> 09:16.896
When you get older and wiser,

09:16.898 --> 09:19.298
you'll realize that's why
I play poker with them.

09:19.300 --> 09:21.600
Look, Harp, I came here to
talk to you about something.

09:21.602 --> 09:23.502
What, about your bad haircut?

09:23.504 --> 09:25.771
Don't start with my hair again.
I like my hair.

09:25.773 --> 09:26.806
It's perfect.

09:26.808 --> 09:27.807
Perfect.

09:27.809 --> 09:28.975
It's current.

09:28.977 --> 09:30.309
I blend in.

09:30.311 --> 09:32.511
I look like a regular guy
at Wal-Mart.

09:32.513 --> 09:35.081
Wal-Mart, 1972 maybe.

09:35.083 --> 09:36.615
Okay, can we get
out of here?

09:36.617 --> 09:37.984
I am here to shoot.

09:55.136 --> 09:56.936
Really.

09:56.938 --> 09:59.005
I'm serious, Harp.
It's important.

09:59.007 --> 10:01.774
And what do I owe the pleasure
of you ruining my Saturday?

10:01.776 --> 10:03.542
My teenage daughter.

10:03.544 --> 10:07.279
My Saturday's fucked.

10:08.883 --> 10:12.284
I go by Cate's recital.
She's a no show.

10:12.286 --> 10:14.787
All I want is for my daughter
to be able to handle

10:14.789 --> 10:16.455
the things that come
at her in life.

10:16.457 --> 10:18.124
Well, call me crazy,

10:18.126 --> 10:20.292
but what about talking
to the ex?

10:20.294 --> 10:21.794
Where's the fucking gun?

10:21.796 --> 10:23.062
Oh, Nicky.

10:23.064 --> 10:24.830
I've tried to reach out
a couple times

10:24.832 --> 10:27.166
to have a conversation,
and she just goes nuclear.

10:27.168 --> 10:28.534
You're never going
to resolve this

10:28.536 --> 10:30.369
if you guys can't even
talk to each other,

10:30.371 --> 10:32.405
which, by the way,
is all kids want.

10:32.407 --> 10:35.374
They want their parents
to get along,

10:35.376 --> 10:37.043
or at least be able to talk.

10:37.045 --> 10:39.145
Look, Harper, I get it.
I'm a crook.

10:39.147 --> 10:40.913
We made a deal,
and a deal's a deal.

10:40.915 --> 10:43.049
Things have taken a turn
for the worse.

10:43.051 --> 10:44.350
So what's different?

10:44.352 --> 10:46.085
What's different now
is that her mom,

10:46.087 --> 10:48.254
she's checked into rehab,
she's doing a stint,

10:48.256 --> 10:49.922
and Cate's a teenager.

10:49.924 --> 10:52.558
She's a 16 year old, Harper,
with 16-year-old problems.

10:52.560 --> 10:54.860
She's got boobs
and hormones.

10:54.862 --> 10:57.763
She's hanging out with a group
of dopey kids making bad choices.

10:57.765 --> 11:00.533
She needs some guidance
in life, but I wouldn't be good at that.

11:00.535 --> 11:02.334
I don't know how to
teach her that stuff.

11:02.336 --> 11:04.737
It's a fucking problem.

11:09.710 --> 11:11.677
What I wanna know is how the
hell did you convince your mom

11:11.679 --> 11:13.919
to let you stay here
by yourself?

11:14.849 --> 11:16.515
Well, when your mom's
packing for detox,

11:16.517 --> 11:19.285
you can pretty much get her
to sign off on anything.

11:19.287 --> 11:22.254
Like, what do you do when you're
all by yourself and you get bored?

11:22.256 --> 11:24.256
Since I don't have
any family around,

11:24.258 --> 11:26.592
what I always do...
go to Becca's.

11:26.594 --> 11:28.027
Cheers to that.

11:34.435 --> 11:36.735
Seriously, no shit like that.

11:36.737 --> 11:40.539
Who cares?
I won. I won, Jeremy.

11:40.541 --> 11:42.942
Let's go, Jeremy. Keys.

11:42.944 --> 11:44.477
All right, look.
This is my baby.

11:44.479 --> 11:46.045
Is it your baby?

11:46.047 --> 11:47.379
Well, you should probably
wash it more often.

11:47.381 --> 11:49.381
Come on, keys.

11:49.383 --> 11:51.317
Oh, you actually got the keys.

11:54.555 --> 11:56.322
Where are we going?

12:04.165 --> 12:05.498
Hey, Harp.

12:05.500 --> 12:07.099
Alejandro is dead.

12:07.101 --> 12:08.167
<i>What?</i>

12:08.169 --> 12:10.002
<i>He's dead.</i>

12:10.004 --> 12:11.237
They're all dead.

12:11.239 --> 12:12.571
You got a problem.

12:12.573 --> 12:14.140
<i>You've been framed, Nick.</i>

12:14.142 --> 12:16.502
<i>Meet me at your place
in five minutes.</i>

12:19.113 --> 12:22.314
What the fuck is going on here?
My hands aren't in this thing.

12:22.316 --> 12:26.085
Alejandro's father
is Victor Vasquez.

12:26.087 --> 12:29.522
He's the head of a major
drug cartel in Mexico.

12:29.524 --> 12:33.926
There are cemeteries in business
because of Victor Vasquez.

12:33.928 --> 12:36.996
Now, this guy
is very dangerous,

12:36.998 --> 12:39.165
and we don't know
what he thinks happened.

12:39.167 --> 12:41.100
This is a Christmas card

12:41.102 --> 12:43.135
he sends out when
someone crosses him.

12:43.137 --> 12:46.338
Serves as a message to anyone
who might do the same.

12:46.340 --> 12:49.141
He's not someone
you want coming after you.

12:49.143 --> 12:51.343
Look, I'm the one
that provides for Cate.

12:51.345 --> 12:53.345
If anything was to happen to me,
worst-case scenario,

12:53.347 --> 12:55.347
I've got to make sure
that she's taken care of.

12:55.349 --> 12:57.216
Oh, Nick.

12:57.218 --> 12:59.451
I think I got a move.
I can do it quick.

12:59.453 --> 13:02.388
Then you go.
You go and you go quick.

13:06.894 --> 13:09.028
What is it that you're
looking for, Mr. Barrow?

13:09.030 --> 13:11.697
Something for
the immediate future.

13:11.699 --> 13:15.834
All right, well then,
I would suggest our term life policy.

13:15.836 --> 13:19.638
A premium on a $500,000
life insurance policy would be...

13:19.640 --> 13:21.106
Does that cover me?

13:23.144 --> 13:24.577
What's next?

13:24.579 --> 13:26.078
You have
any felony convictions

13:26.080 --> 13:28.347
less than three years ago?
Do you skydive?

13:28.349 --> 13:29.348
No.

13:29.350 --> 13:30.916
Are you a pilot?
No.

13:30.918 --> 13:33.886
Do you drink? Smoke?
Well, more than I should

13:33.888 --> 13:35.688
but not always enough.

13:35.690 --> 13:37.723
I assume that carries
an overage premium?

13:37.725 --> 13:40.426
It does.
Okay. What else?

13:41.929 --> 13:45.164
Well, I guess the name
of your beneficiary.

13:45.166 --> 13:47.900
Cate... uh, Catherine.
Catherine Jill Barrow.

13:47.902 --> 13:51.570
This is the name of her bank.

13:51.572 --> 13:54.106
Her account number,
and I'd like to prepay any taxes.

13:56.177 --> 13:58.177
All right.
Well, um...

13:58.179 --> 14:00.412
I will write up
the policy, file it,

14:00.414 --> 14:02.448
and pending your blood work
in about three weeks,

14:02.450 --> 14:04.450
you will get confirmation
of your coverage.

14:04.452 --> 14:07.519
After that,
you can jaywalk all you want.

14:09.857 --> 14:13.626
Charger. It's used.
Tags. Gas. Plates are clean.

14:13.628 --> 14:15.261
Where is it?

14:15.263 --> 14:16.962
Alley behind Derian's.

14:16.964 --> 14:18.197
You be smart.

14:18.199 --> 14:19.932
Then lay low
at the safe house

14:19.934 --> 14:21.800
till we can see
how this plays out.

14:28.142 --> 14:29.775
Yeah.

14:29.777 --> 14:33.012
<i>Mr. Barrow, do you know
who this is?</i>

14:34.248 --> 14:35.881
How did you get this number?

14:35.883 --> 14:38.217
<i>I know people.</i>

14:38.219 --> 14:39.885
<i>We need to talk, Nick.</i>

14:39.887 --> 14:41.553
Isn't that what
we're doing now?

14:41.555 --> 14:42.955
<i>In person.</i>

14:42.957 --> 14:44.456
Impossible.

14:44.458 --> 14:46.392
<i>I've been doing this
a long time,</i>

14:46.394 --> 14:48.060
<i>and you know what I've learned?</i>
What?

14:48.062 --> 14:50.095
<i>That anything is possible.</i>

15:08.949 --> 15:10.749
<i>Being interrogated
by a cartel leader</i>

15:10.751 --> 15:13.919
<i>is not how I expected
my day to start out.</i>

15:13.921 --> 15:16.522
<i>This is bad, really bad.</i>

15:16.524 --> 15:18.857
<i>All I could do was try
my best to stay calm,</i>

15:18.859 --> 15:21.627
<i>keep my mouth shut,
and not rat out Jimmy Lincoln.</i>

15:21.629 --> 15:23.829
<i>I've been around
long enough to know,</i>

15:23.831 --> 15:26.565
<i>you start talking,
you end up dead.</i>

15:50.191 --> 15:52.291
Mr. Barrow.

15:52.293 --> 15:54.293
Nick.

15:54.295 --> 15:56.528
Can I call you Nick?

15:56.530 --> 15:58.430
Yeah.

15:59.867 --> 16:02.534
I'm going to ask you
a few questions.

16:02.536 --> 16:03.569
We're just talking.

16:03.571 --> 16:06.305
And you answer them honestly...

16:08.309 --> 16:10.209
and we're fine.

16:10.211 --> 16:12.010
You go your way,
I'll go mine.

16:12.012 --> 16:13.045
Hm?

16:14.315 --> 16:16.081
And because I understand

16:16.083 --> 16:18.317
this is an extremely
awkward situation,

16:18.319 --> 16:20.279
I'm going to start
with an easy one.

16:24.392 --> 16:26.552
Who else did you sell
the job to?

16:27.895 --> 16:29.661
No one.

16:39.440 --> 16:41.607
You don't, uh...

16:41.609 --> 16:44.376
It doesn't go like that.

16:44.378 --> 16:47.212
I didn't find the job,
I just planned it.

16:47.214 --> 16:48.647
Who found this one?

16:58.692 --> 17:01.693
Then that puts us at a bit
of a crossroads, my friend.

17:05.366 --> 17:08.567
I know deep down...
I know you know something.

17:08.569 --> 17:11.804
A name, an address, a number.
Something.

17:13.973 --> 17:15.307
I don't know.

17:25.219 --> 17:27.618
I feel I can tell you
that at some point

17:27.621 --> 17:29.902
I'm gonna end up
losing my patience.

17:35.296 --> 17:38.664
"Catherine." Wife?

17:38.666 --> 17:39.998
Victor, listen to me.

17:40.000 --> 17:41.600
Or daughter?
Listen to me.

17:41.602 --> 17:43.669
I designed it,
that's it.

17:43.671 --> 17:45.037
Daughter.

17:55.850 --> 17:58.116
We're making progress.

17:58.118 --> 18:01.153
So I'll tell you what,
I'm gonna get your daughter.

18:01.155 --> 18:03.055
In the meantime...

18:04.492 --> 18:06.158
make yourself at home.

18:10.631 --> 18:11.697
Good.

18:13.434 --> 18:15.067
I feel good about this.

18:53.207 --> 18:54.973
I'm gonna get some water.

18:54.975 --> 18:56.041
I'm just gonna...

18:56.043 --> 18:57.643
Easy, easy.

19:14.728 --> 19:16.194
Don't do it!
Stand! Stay!

19:16.196 --> 19:17.563
Stop it!

19:29.043 --> 19:31.076
Victor found me.
He thinks I double sold the job.

19:31.078 --> 19:32.678
Someone else put
their hands in this.

19:32.680 --> 19:34.680
<i>Where's Jimmy Lincoln?</i>
I don't know.

19:34.682 --> 19:37.015
I need you to find him
for me. Cate's not safe.

19:37.017 --> 19:38.050
Where is she?

19:38.052 --> 19:39.484
I'm going to get her now.

19:52.933 --> 19:54.533
Cate, it's okay.

19:54.535 --> 19:56.034
Please, we gotta go.
They're going to be here soon.

19:56.036 --> 19:57.235
Who's gonna be here soon?

19:57.237 --> 19:58.604
Guys that're trying
to kill me.

19:58.606 --> 20:00.038
What the hell are
you doing here?

20:00.040 --> 20:01.280
Okay, listen.
We got to... Cate!

20:02.443 --> 20:04.076
Cate, please!

20:04.078 --> 20:05.477
We gotta get out of here.

20:06.714 --> 20:08.046
Cate...

20:09.416 --> 20:11.550
What, are you kidnapping me?

20:11.552 --> 20:12.884
I'm not kidnapping you.

20:12.886 --> 20:14.886
Parents kidnap kids
all the time.

20:19.593 --> 20:21.393
I'm sorry.
We gotta go quick.

20:33.474 --> 20:35.340
Let's go.
No, fuck this.

20:35.342 --> 20:37.809
I'm not moving until
you tell me what's going on.

20:37.811 --> 20:39.444
Cate, trust me.
It's a long story,

20:39.446 --> 20:41.246
